author: Casey Chan on Sploid, shared by Casey Chan to Gizmodo
title: Watch the World's First Double Backflip on a Snowmobile
text:
Go to permalink GIF 
Snowmobiles weigh over 450 pounds so flipping them once in mid-air is already insanity, but Daniel Bodin wanted to do something nobody else has ever done, so he went for it and nailed a double backflip on a snowmobile. It’s a helluva trick that’s been attempted back in 2009 and 2011 at the X-Games but hasn’t ever been landed before like this. Advertisement
